---
description: Enforce small frequent commits, test-before-push, and semver release discipline
globs:
  - ".githooks/*"
  - "scripts/check_commit_scope.py"
  - "scripts/install_hooks.py"
  - "scripts/release_semver.py"
  - ".github/workflows/semver-release.yml"
  - "VERSION"
  - "README.md"
alwaysApply: true
---

- Keep commits small and targeted by default. Split broad work into sequenced commits by concern (data, pipeline, UI, docs).
- Use Conventional Commits (`type(scope): summary`) so semver automation can classify changes.
- Protect push quality: run validator/compile checks before push; never push known-failing state.
- Keep hook logic lightweight and cross-platform where practical (repo scripts + minimal shell wrapper).
- If hook behavior changes, update README workflow docs in same change.
- `VERSION` is source of truth for release version and is bumped automatically from commit intent on `main`.
- Semver bump policy:
  - breaking (`!` or `BREAKING CHANGE`) -> major
  - `feat` -> minor
  - `fix`/`perf`/`refactor`/`data`/`docs`/`test`/`chore`/`ci`/`build`/`style` -> patch
